@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Our Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p>At EduManage, we take the privacy and security of our users' personal information very seriously. This privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect the information we obtain through our student record management software.</p>

    <h2>1. Information Collection</h2>
    <p>We collect personal information from EduManage users, which may include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Names</li>
        <li>Addresses</li>
        <li>Email addresses</li>
        <li>Phone numbers</li>
        <li>Academic information</li>
        <li>Other relevant data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This information is collected to provide and improve our services.</p>

    <h2>2. Use of Information</h2>
    <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Manage and maintain student records.</li>
        <li>Provide technical support and assistance.</li>
        <li>Improve and personalize the user experience.</li>
        <li>Communicate with users about updates and news related to EduManage.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Information Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not share users' personal information with third parties, except in the following cases:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>With the explicit consent of the user.</li>
        <li>When required to comply with legal obligations.</li>
        <li>To protect the rights, property, or safety of EduManage and its users.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Information Security</h2>
    <p>We implement technical and organizational security measures to protect users' personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.</p>

    <h2>5. User Rights</h2>
    <p>Users have the right to access, correct, or delete their personal information stored in EduManage. To exercise these rights, users can contact our support team.</p>

    <h2>6. Changes to the Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to update this privacy policy at any time. We will notify users of any significant changes through our platform or via email.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:mario.suerodejesus@gmail.com">Mario.suerodejesus@gmail.com</a>.</p>
</body>
</html>
